      "raw_text": "zone satisfied farmer brought\ninto this Inland Empire today is\nworth $4,000; one dissatisfied man\nhere will offest.\"\n\n\nSuch was the observation given\nthe chamber of commerce this noon\nby Herbert Myrick. editor of the\nOrange-Judd Farmer. Mr.. Myrick\ninveighed against discrimination of\nIndustrial class interests, as OPP\nposed to the agriculturist. He\nclosed by making tribute to the\nfruitfulness Of the Inland Empire.\nwhich was received with applause.\n\n\nYou applaud this sentiment\"\nsaid Mr.. Myrick, shut you should\nalso heed some of the criticisms\nmade in the beginning about all\nclasses here working together in\nharmony Of interests. In the ulti-\nmate result, the man on the land\nis the one to look to-\""
